---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Pricing — idr.to">
  <Header slot="header" />
  <Footer slot="footer" />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Plans</p>
      <h1>Pricing</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Signaling unlocks registry, ACLs, and WebRTC introduction. Data transfer bundles are optional and only
        required when traffic must flow through TURN or HTTPS relay — not for direct P2P.
      </p>

      <div class="card-grid card-grid--2" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
        <div class="card pricing-card">
          <span class="badge">Personal</span>
          <p class="pricing-card__price">US$5 <span>/ year</span></p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Single-level host</strong> — e.g. <code>laptop~you@example.com</code></li>
            <li>One user, up to <strong>5 devices</strong> — <a href="/addressing#multiple-devices">one host per machine</a></li>
            <li>Hosted signaling + STUN</li>
            <li>Same-entity access by default</li>
            <li>P2P data plane included (no per-GB charge)</li>
            <li>Read-only web portal</li>
          </ul>
          <a class="btn btn--primary" href="/checkout?plan=personal">Purchase Personal</a>
        </div>
        <div class="card pricing-card">
          <span class="badge">Enterprise</span>
          <p class="pricing-card__price">US$50 <span>/ user / year</span></p>
          <p style="margin:0;color:var(--text-muted);font-size:0.875rem;">or <strong>US$5 / user / month</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Multi-level hosts</strong> — e.g. <code>db1.us-east.finance~corp.com</code></li>
            <li>One user, up to <strong>5 devices</strong> — <a href="/addressing#multiple-devices">one host per machine</a></li>
            <li>Cross-entity ACL management</li>
            <li>Subdomain entity delegation</li>
            <li>Org-wide access keys &amp; audit</li>
            <li>Priority support</li>
          </ul>
          <a class="btn btn--primary" href="/checkout?plan=enterprise">Purchase Enterprise</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Data transfer bundles</h2>
      <p>For traffic that cannot travel P2P and must use TURN or HTTPS edge relay:</p>
      <div class="card" style="max-width: 32rem;">
        <p class="pricing-card__price" style="margin:0;">US$10 <span>/ 500 GB bundle</span></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Buy as many 500 GB bundles as you need</li>
          <li><strong>Unused data rolls over</strong> to the next month for up to <strong>12 months</strong></li>
          <li>Metered: TURN relay + HTTPS mux (https-relay)</li>
          <li>Not consumed by direct WebRTC P2P connections</li>
        </ul>
        <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="/checkout?plan=data-500">Add 500 GB bundle</a>
      </div>

      <div class="callout" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
        <strong>No data bundle?</strong> Your target hosts remain fully accessible on <strong>peer-to-peer</strong>
        connections when the network allows ICE. You only need bundles when you rely on relayed paths.
      </div>

      <h2>30-day evaluation</h2>
      <p>
        New accounts receive <strong>30 days of signaling-only</strong> access — registry, ACLs, WebRTC signaling, and P2P.
        No credit card required. Relay data bundles are not included during trial; purchase after evaluation ends.
      </p>
      <a class="btn btn--primary" href="/evaluate">Start free evaluation</a>

      <h2>What's included everywhere</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Ed25519 Device-ID &amp; Host-Identity (<code>host~entity-id</code>)</li>
        <li>WebRTC idr-tunnel-v1 (TCP + UDP-style segments)</li>
        <li>CLI (<code>idr</code>), Rust agent, optional https-relay (self-hosted or managed)</li>
        <li>Browser SDK &amp; Dart SDK (see <a href="/isv">ISV page</a>)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <p>Common billing questions are answered in the <a href="/faq#billing">FAQ</a>. API entitlements: <a href="/billing">billing reference</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  h1 { font-size: 2.25rem; margin: 0 0 1rem; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.5rem; margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem; }
  ul { color: var(--text-muted); }
</style>
